The paper deals with a logic for specifying and verifying properties of hybrid games, which involve both discrete and continuous dynamics and adversarial players. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Game Theory (cs.GT), and Control Systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of dGL for studying winning strategies, which suggests a connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.MS) as well.
